Africa, although people with HIV still live 5 years to 10 years less than those 
without HIV, and new cost-effectiveness research revealed that the price of 
antiretroviral therapy itself remains a key driver of cost and 
cost-effectiveness calculations. Results from the PROMISE trial showed reduced 
rates of mother-to-child transmission among women who received antiretroviral 
therapy with 3 drugs compared with women who received zidovudine monotherapy, 
